# {{ project_name }}

React + Vite frontend with an Express backend, scaffolded with [creo](https://github.com/creo-cli/creo).

## Stack

- **Frontend**: React 18, Vite 5, port `{{ frontend_port }}`
- **Backend**: Express 4 on port `{{ backend_port }}`, `/api/*` proxied from the frontend
- **Hot reload**: source bind-mounted into both containers

## Setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env
creo start {{ project_name }}
```

Then open <http://localhost:{{ frontend_port }}>.

## Useful commands

```bash
creo logs {{ project_name }}                  # follow logs
creo logs {{ project_name }} --service backend
creo shell {{ project_name }} --service backend
creo run  {{ project_name }} npm test
creo stop {{ project_name }}
```

## Layout

```
src/main.jsx       – React entry point
server/index.js    – Express API (/health, /api/hello)
vite.config.js     – dev server + /api proxy to backend
docker-compose.yml – frontend + backend services
```

